---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Theming" currentSlug="theming">
  <h1>Theming</h1>
  <p>
    Light, dark, and system modes are fully functional, persisted
    locally, and synced to the native Tauri window chrome on both macOS
    and Windows via <code>getCurrentWindow().setTheme()</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>No flash of the wrong theme</h2>
  <p>
    The mode is applied in a blocking <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> script
    before first paint, so there's no flash of the wrong theme on load.
    The same script also applies the sidebar's collapsed/expanded state
    before paint, for the same reason.
  </p>

  <h2>CSS variables</h2>
  <p>
    All chrome components theme via <code>--cc-*</code> custom
    properties defined once in <code>AppShellLayout.astro</code>, not
    hardcoded colors, so both palettes stay consistent everywhere.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
